<br>
While a Druid may have utility spells they are quite linear in nature. Also druid do not have a spell for every occation either. &lt;Also has a 55 druid&gt; <br>
<br>
Bards are unique to the world of Norrath. The ablility to juggle 3 songs maybe a 4th on a good day. The ability to run faster than anything on the planet, to heal, mana regen, Dot, even dd a little, kite, fear kit, mez, charm, occasionally stun, create dmg shields, str/agil/dex buff, mini rune, haste, invis, evade, lull pull, debuff, slow, snare, Group invul &lt;at lvl 60&gt; shadow step, melee a bit as well and are GODS of resist. There are few other things we can do but is restricted by time of day. Bards make others Stronger around them. Their songs stack with spells that normally dont allow other spells to stack with them. <br>
<br>
Bards are still not well understood and those that have a twink lvl 20 bard still have no real clue to what they can do. Bards have very defining moments in their career where they go through a serious metamorphasis at several stages. While for pure power, most classes are more powerful, I cannot count how many times the bard has saved the day. I cannot count how many times I have been told, &quot;Wow, I did not know you could do that&quot; when saving the day. <br>
<br>
I read threads where the question is.... What songs do you mainly use? I hate this question. It show a lack of understanding of the class. That question is so hard to answer because it depends on the situation. What mobs are you fighting? What is your group composition? What zone are you in? Is it day or night? What race are the members of your Group? There are several permutations for a bard. Once again a song for every occasion. Bards limit down time severly and can fill the role of about every class. Cleric being the one we really cannot compensate for. But In the past when I have been in groups with no cleric and have a shaman and another decent healer, I have been known to whip out the banjo and twist Niv's and Catana to keep the group at full health. Only the necro seems to have close to this much versatility. <br>
<br>
Our strenght lies in our subtlety, most have no clue to what we are even doing for them. I have received many a tell where after I left the group saying, &quot;Man we were killing so much faster with you in the group.&quot; Now if we just had a group intra zone succor song that would rule. he he<br>
<br>
Also the bard is the only class I know of that can help a group while AFK as well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Hopefully this will give a better understanding of the bard. I know there are other very competent bards out there that could probably add to this and I have not mentioned everything we can do and definately not in detail. Of all the classes I have played the bard is still my favorite hands down bar none. Even when we had the XP penalties, I would not have given up my bard for the world. There are some minor tweaks I would like to see done for the bard but other than that they by far take the most skill and attention to detail of any other class in the game.<br>
